Jeffrey M. (Jeff) Blackburn 

		
		SVP, Business Development, 

	
		 Amazon.com, Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 07/11/2017 



Executive Summary
Blackburn has been Amazon.com's Senior Vice President, Business Development, since April 2006 - and Vice President, Business Development, for two years before. He's had a hand in virtually all of Amazon.com's business developing activities, from its hugely successful Kindle e-book reader to its new cloud music storage servi 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Blackburn is married to Anne Fleischli. They live in Seattle, Washington, with their two daughters, Kate and Kendall.
He was a three-year starter and All-Ivy outside linebacker for Dartmouth Football. He played on the 1990 team 
Current Focus

Enter into wine business: Amazon is getting  
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1970.
Blackburn earned his bachelor's degree in economics and public policy from Dartmouth College and his master's in business administration from Stanford Graduate School of Business. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Board of Directors, Wikia, Inc.
Member, Board of Directors, WhoSay, Inc. 
 





